                "invention-title": [
                    "Preparation method and application of modified silicon-based catalyst",
                    "一种改性硅基催化剂的制备方法及应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a preparation method of a modified silicon-based catalyst, which comprises the following steps: sequentially adding nickel salt, cobalt salt and ethidene diamine into deionized water, uniformly mixing, adding a silicon-based carrier, uniformly stirring and mixing, drying, adding a template agent and water into the dried material, carrying out wet grinding for 10-20 minutes, treating the ground material at 100-120 DEG C for 40-55 hours, taking out, drying and calcining to obtain the modified silicon-based catalyst. Reducing the calcined product in a hydrogen atmosphere at 700-800 DEG C to obtain a silicon-based catalyst; the catalyst prepared by the invention is high in active metal utilization rate, high in sintering resistance and carbon deposition resistance, and excellent in activity and stability in methane reforming reaction; the catalyst can stably catalyze for at least 100 hours without obvious inactivation no matter under the conditions of high temperature of 750 DEG C and easy sintering or 650 DEG C and easy carbon deposition, and has a good application prospect in the aspects of energy and environment."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开一种改性硅基催化剂的制备方法，该方法是将镍盐、钴盐、乙二胺依次添加到去离子水中混匀后，加入硅基载体，搅拌混匀后干燥，在干燥物中加入模板剂、水，湿法研磨10~20min，研磨后材料在100~120℃下处理40~55h后，取出干燥煅烧，煅烧产物在氢气气氛、700℃~800℃下还原制得硅基催化剂；本发明制备的催化剂的活性金属利用率高，抗烧结、积碳能力强，在甲烷重整反应中具有优异的活性和稳定性；该催化剂不管是在750℃高温易烧结条件下，还是650℃易积碳条件下都能稳定催化至少100h未明显失活，在能源和环境方面具有良好的应用前景。"
                }
            ]
